TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cochrane, John H.
T1  - Permanent and Transitory Components of GNP and Stock Prices*
PY  - 1994
Y1  - 1994/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118434
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 109
IS  - 1
SP  - 241
EP  - 265
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper uses two-variable autoregressions to characterize transitory components in GNP and stock prices. Shocks to GNP holding consumption constant are almost entirely transitory, and account for large fractions of the variance of GNP growth. If consumption does not change, consumers must think that any GNP change is transitory. The facts that the consumption/GNP ratio forecasts GNP growth and that consumption is nearly a random walk drive this result. An implication is that consumption provides a good estimate of the “trend” in GNP. Prices and dividends behave similarly: shocks to prices holding dividends constant are almost entirely transitory.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118434
ER  - 



